  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oven to 325˚F (160˚C). </step>
    <step num="1">In medium bowl, add coconut flakes, soy sauce, maple syrup, and liquid smoke. Mix until thoroughly coated. </step>
    <step num="2">Grease pan with coconut oil. Spread the coated coconut flakes in a thin layer onto a baking sheet. </step>
    <step num="3">Bake for 10-15 minutes, flipping every five minutes until golden brown. </step>
    <step num="4">Serve with your favorite dish. </step>
    <step num="5">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
